    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-17T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-17T19:00:00-05:00" n="912"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d912">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.248/812: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-17T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >December 17, 1942—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>664. To be decoded by the Ambassador. Your 1295, December 15 and 1302, December
                    16. Your reports have been conveyed to General Arnold, who is most appreciative
                    of your efforts. He is issuing instructions to American military authorities in
                    Cairo to return plane to Turkey. Different crew in civilian clothes will be
                    used, and personnel will be supplied with American passports and Turkish
                    visas.</p>
                <pb facs="0816" n="804" xml:id="pg_804"/>
                <p>The War Department is taking this action in view of your understanding that new
                    crew will not be subject to internment under this procedure.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
